
Framework----

A framework is a standard project structure created to manage automation scripts in reusable , maintenable, and scalable ways...

Reusable-
Lines of code, can be reuse with the help of page object model, testdata, utility

Manintenable-
if we have change in locator or method logic then we can update single locator or single method,
so it is easy to maintain if we have framework structure.

Scalability-
today we have 2 test case login , add employee,
after few days  we will have around 20 test cases so same framework can be used and it will grow as per requirements in future...

POM------------------------------------------
Page object model is design pattern which seprates the test logics from locators and mthods...
pages can have all elemements locators present on this particular page 
for example if we have loginPage then all webElements present on this page can be store in loginPage class and the we can write number of login page test scenarios..
no need to define and store it again and again in every login test...


Page Manager Concept
Test Data driven approach by using testData.json file
Faker class utility approach



